history.content: Have you posted on the 16B Piazza regarding resources?

I am currently a student in EECS 16B and I noticed that there is a really low number of tutors and mentors for this class, apart from the existing TA's and ASEs. A big resource that has helped me in my past CS/EECS classes has been the mentoring groups such as CSM, HKN, and CAEE. However, I noticed that there was an extremely low number of CSM mentors for 16b this semester, and there is not a single tutor for 16b in CAEE.

16b is known for being a time-consuming and content-heavy class, and I would assume a lot of students could use extra help to do well to supplement their understanding of the interesting material in this class. 

I would highly appreciate it if more students who took 16b in the past could sign up for CSM/CAEE. It would extremely help a lot of us. Also, are there any other resources outside the classroom that I am missing out on for this class?
history.subject: EE16B mentors and support
